shapes:RentalOfferTemplateShape
    a sh:NodeShape ;
    sh:targetClass ids:RentalOffer ;
    sh:node shapes:HasProviderOrConsumerNodeShape ;
    sh:property shapes:RentalOfferTemplate-permissionPropertyShape ;
    sh:message "<https://raw.githubusercontent.com/International-Data-Spaces-Association/InformationModel/master/examples/contract-and-usage-policy/templates/RentalTemplates/RentalOfferTemplateShape.ttl> (RentalOfferTemplateShape): In a _:RentalOffer a) the ids:provider property must point to one participant or b) the ids:consumer property must point to one participant or c) the ids:provider and the ids:consumer must point to one participant. This can in any case be a) an IRI or b) an ids:Participant. The ids:permission property must point to at exactly one ids:Permission. In the ids:Permission ids:target and ids:action properties and at least one of (ids:assigner or ids:assignee) pointing to a participant have to be specified. The ids:constraint property must point to an ids:Constraint with ids:leftOperand idsc:STATE, ids:operator idsc:NOT, ids:rightOperand specifying a termination state as an entity representing the (final) state of the contract and zero or one ids:pipEndpoint property pointing to a PipUri. In the Permission the ids:preDuty property must point to an ids:Duty with at least one of (ids:assigner or ids:assignee) pointing to a participant, ids:action pointing to ids:Action (1) and the ids:constraint property must point to an ids:Constraint (2). Within the ids:Action (1) the ids:includedIn property must point to idsc:COMPENSATE and the ids:actionRefinement property must point to an ids:Constraint (3). Within the ids:Action (1) the ids:Constraint (3) must have ids:leftOperand pointing to idsc:PAY_AMOUNT, ids:operator pointing to idsc:EQ, ids:rightOperand pointing to a fee as xsd:double, ids:unit pointing to an IRI specifying the currency and zero or one ids:pipEndpoint pointing to a PipUri. Within the ids:Duty within the ids:Constraint (2) the ids:leftOperand must point to idsc:POLICY_EVALUATION_TIME, the ids:operator must point to idsc:AFTER and the ids:rightOperand specifies the duration of usage as xsd:duration."@en ;
.


